Privacy Policy for Shamiapp
Last Updated: [Feb 2025]
Thank you for using Shamiapp! We value your trust and are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our app. By using Shamiapp, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.
1. Information We Collect
We want to be transparent about the data we collect and how it’s used. Here’s what we gather:
a. Personal Information
We do not collect personally identifiable information (such as your name, email address, or phone number) unless you voluntarily provide it to us (e.g., through feedback or support requests).
b. Non-Personal Information
We may collect non-personal information, such as:
Device information (e.g., device model, operating system version).
App usage data (e.g., features used, time spent in the app).
Anonymous analytics data to improve app performance and user experience.
c. Permissions
Shamiapp may request certain permissions to function properly. These include:
Internet Access: To provide app functionality and load content.
[Add other permissions your app uses, if any, e.g., Storage, Location, etc.]
We do not misuse these permissions or access data unrelated to the app’s functionality.
2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used to:
Improve the app’s performance and user experience.
Respond to your feedback or support requests.
Analyze app usage to fix bugs and add new features.
Ensure the app functions as intended.
3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We respect your privacy and do not share your personal information with third parties, except in the following cases:
With Your Consent: If you give us permission to share your information.
For Legal Reasons: If required by law or to protect our rights and safety.
Service Providers: We may use third-party services (e.g., analytics tools) that collect non-personal data to help us improve the app. These providers are obligated to protect your data.
4. Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of data transmission or storage is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.
5. Children’s Privacy
Shamiapp is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with their information, please contact us, and we will take steps to delete it.
6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you through the app or via email (if provided). Please review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:
Email: [khanshami405@gmail.com]
Thank you for trusting Shamiapp! We’re here to provide you with a great experience while keeping your privacy a top priority.
